article.headline: IUPUI 70, W. Illinois 42
article.story: MACOMB, Ill -- Robert Glenn scored 27 points and Alex Young 20 as IUPUI routed Western Illinois 70-42 on Saturday night. Glenn shot 8-for-10 from the floor and 11-for-14 from the line for the Jaguars (17-8, 10-2 Summit League), who have won seven of their last eight. Young shot 8-for-11, including two 3-pointers. Leroy Nobles added 10 points, and John Ashworth had a game-high 10 assists. David Nurse scored 17 points for the Leathernecks (9-14, 2-10). IUPUI never trailed. The Jaguars led 34-20 at halftime, scored the first eight points of the second half to go up 42-20 and enjoyed their largest lead at 65-29 on Glenn's basket with 6:18 to play. IUPUI has won 22 of the last 23 meetings between the schools, including a 67-54 victory Jan. 9. The Jaguars shot 59.5 percent and remained undefeated this season when shooting at least 50 percent (12-0) and leading at halftime (14-0).
